name				addbordertoimage
version				0.1-1
architecture			x86_gcc2

summary			"Add a border to images"
Description			"A small applet to add a coloured border to an image and save the resulting image, using ImageMagick.

The non-interactive script will grab the default saved from the GUI version. If this does not exist, it defaults to a black border 20 pixels thick.

Currently the preview window may cut off the bottom of the graphic, but you can always use the View button.

Planned to be part of a larger graphics workflow application, but can be used standalone.

Menu position: Applications | Graphics
"

packager			"Michel Clasquin-Johnson <clasqm@mail.com>"
